ass=\"recipe\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Recipe\">\n<h1 itemprop=\"name\">Purple Potato Chips</h1>\n<div class=\"socialButtons\">\n<div class=\"fb-like\" data-send=\"false\" data-href=\"http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/purple-potato-chips/\" data-layout=\"button_count\" data-width=\"105\" data-show-faces=\"false\" data-action=\"like\"></div>\n<div class=\"pinterest\">\n<a href=\"http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.makebetterfood.com%2Frecipes%2Fpurple-potato-chips%2F&media=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.makebetterfood.com/recipes/purple-potato-chips/purple-potato-chips_large.jpg&description=Purple%20Potato%20Chips\" class=\"pin-it-button\" count-layout=\"horizontal\">Pin It</a>\n</div>\n<div class=\"print\"><a href=\"/pdfs/purple-potato-chips.pdf\" onclick=\"logPrintEvent('Purple Potato Chips');\"><img src=\"/img/icons/print.png\" alt=\"Print\" /></a><a href=\"/pdfs/purple-potato-chips.pdf\" onclick=\"logPrintEvent('Purple Potato Chips');\">Print or download (PDF)</a></div>\n</div>\n<ul class=\"breadcrumbs\">\n<li><a href=\"/\">Home</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/\">Recipes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/appetizers/\"><span itemprop=\"recipeCategory\">Appetizers</span></a></li>\n<li>Purple Potato Chips</li>\n</ul>\n<div itemprop=\"description\" class=\"description\">When you have fresh purple potatoes, it's only natural to turn them into delicious homemade potato chips.</div>\n<div class=\"stats\">\n<ul>\n<li>Prep: <meta itemprop=\"prepTime\" value=\"PT15M\"/>15 min</li>\n<li>Chill: <meta itemprop=\"chillTime\" value=\"PT20M\"/>20 min</li>\n<li>Cook: <meta itemprop=\"cookTime\" value=\"PT15M\"/>15 min</li>\n<li>Total: <meta itemprop=\"totalTime\" value=\"PT50M\"/>50 min</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeYield\">Serves 4</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"steps\">\n<div class=\"right\">\n<a href=\"/recipes/purple-potato-chips/purple-potato-chips_large.jpg\"><img class=\"polaroid\" src=\"/recipes/purple-potato-chips/purple-potato-chips.jpg\" alt=\"Purple Potato Chips\" itemprop=\"image\"/></a>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"direction\">Preheat oven to 450&deg;F.</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">1 pound purple potatoes (about 5 small)</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Wash and peel potatoes. Cut into 1/16-inch thick slices with a mandoline or a sharp knife. Place cut potato slices in a large bowl.</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">1 tablespoon olive oil</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">&frac12; teaspoon kosher salt</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Toss potatoes with olive oil and salt until well coated.</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Arrange slices in a single large on a rimmed baking sheet. If you have a wire rack, you can use it to improve air circulation and ensure even cooking.</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Bake at 450&deg;F until chips are starting to brown on the edges, about 15 to 18 minutes.</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Remove from oven and place on a wire rack to cool, about 20 minutes, before serving.</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">If chips are not crispy enough, return to oven to bake at 450&deg;F for an additional 5 minutes.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"footnote\">\n<div class=\"logo\">MakeBetterFood.com</div>\nFrom MakeBetterFood.com. <time itemprop=\"datePublished\" datetime=\"2012-06-27\">Jun 27, 2012</time>. (http://makebetterfood.com/recipes/purple-potato-chips/).\n</div>\n<!-- Microformat Ingredients -->\n<ul class=\"hidden\">\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">1 pound purple potatoes (about 5 small)</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">1 tablespoon olive oil</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac12; teaspoon kosher salt</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- Microformat Steps -->\n<ol class=\"hidden\">\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Preheat oven to 450&deg;F.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Wash and peel potatoes. Cut into 1/16-inch thick slices with a mandoline or a sharp knife. Place cut potato slices in a large bowl.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Toss potatoes with olive oil and salt until well coated.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Arrange slices in a single large on a rimmed baking sheet. If you have a wire rack, you can use it to improve air circulation and ensure even cooking.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Bake at 450&deg;F until chips are starting to brown on the edges, about 15 to 18 minutes.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Remove from oven and place on a wire rack to cool, about 20 minutes, before serving.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">If chips are not crispy enough, return to oven to bake at 450&deg;F for an additional 5 minutes.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"notPrinted\">\n<div class=\"grid_12\">\n<div class=\"recipe\">\n<h4>Related Equipment or Ingredients</h4>\n<div class=\"pushTop10 clearfix polarioidSummaryRow\">\n<div class=\"polaroidSummary\">\n<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Wear-Ever-Natural-Finish-Aluminum-4x12-7/dp/B0001MS3P6?SubscriptionId=AKIAJT76QZNN5CAIGPSQ&tag=makbetfoo-20&linkCode=xm2&camp=2025&creative=165953&creativeASIN=B0001MS3P6\"><img src=\"http://ecx.images-amazon.com/images/I/21Zmyou77JL.SL100_AA105.jpg\" alt=\"Rimmed Baking Sheet\" class=\"\"/>\nRimmed Baking Sheet</a>\n</div>\n<div class=\"polaroidSummary\">\n<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Swissmar-Borner-V-1001-V-Slicer-Mandoline/dp/B0000632QE?SubscriptionId=AKIAJT76QZNN5CAIGPSQ&tag=makbetfoo-20&linkCode=xm2&camp=2025&creative=165953&creativeASIN=B0000632QE\"><img src=\"http://ecx.images-amazon.com/images/I/315hDZ0XopL.SL100_AA105.jpg\" alt=\"Mandoline\" class=\"\"/>\nMandoline</a>\n</div>\n<div class=\"polaroidSummary\">\n<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/CIA-23304-Masters-Collection-Cooling/dp/B000OFND8W?SubscriptionId=AKIAJT76QZNN5CAIGPSQ&tag=makbetfoo-20&linkCode=xm2&camp=2025&creative=165953&creativeASIN=B000OFND8W\"><img src=\"http://ecx.images-amazon.com/images/I/41D5YP%2B0xcL.SL100_AA105.jpg\" alt=\"Heavy Duty Wire Rack\" class=\"\"/>\nHeavy Duty Wire Rack</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div cl